    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7 and season the chicken with the chilli flakes (can&rsquo;t handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of salt</p> <p><strong>Heat</strong> a large, wide-based pan (with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> vegetable oil</p> <p><strong>Once </strong>hot, cook the chicken for 2 min or until golden brown</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-hoisin-barbecue-chicken/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, slice the pak choi in half, lengthways</p> <p><strong>Transfer </strong>the golden chicken to a baking tray (use tin foil to avoid mess!) and put it in the&nbsp;oven for 12-15 min&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Return</strong>&nbsp;the pan to a high heat and once hot, add the pak choi, cut-side down and cook for 2-3 min or until charred&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Once</strong> done, transfer the pak choi to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-hoisin-barbecue-chicken/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the rice, 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> water and a pinch of salt to a pot with a lid over a high heat and bring to the boil</p> <p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-hoisin-barbecue-chicken/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, dice the plums&nbsp;finely, discarding the stones</p> <p><strong>Return</strong>&nbsp;the pan to a medium-low heat and once hot, add the plums with 100ml<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[200ml]</span>&nbsp;water</p> <p><strong>Cook</strong>&nbsp;for 2-4 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-hoisin-barbecue-chicken/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Add&nbsp;</strong>the hoisin, soy sauce, sesame seeds and&nbsp;1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span>&nbsp;sugar and cook for 1-2 min&nbsp;or until the sauce has a thin jam-like consistency</p> <p><strong>Once</strong>&nbsp;done, remove from the heat and stir in half the toasted sesame oil - this is your hoisin plum sauce</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-hoisin-barbecue-chicken/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Remove </strong>the chicken thighs from the oven and push them to one side of the tray</p> <p><strong>Spoon</strong> a little&nbsp;of the hoisin-plum sauce over each chicken thigh, add the pak choi to the same tray and return the tray to the oven for a final 5 min</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-hoisin-barbecue-chicken/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, slice the spring onion&nbsp;finely, discarding the root ends</p> <p><strong>Once </strong>cooked, fluff&nbsp;the rice with a fork and stir in the spring onion and remaining toasted sesame oil</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-hoisin-barbecue-chicken/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Serve</strong>&nbsp;the chicken over the rice, with the pak choi to the side</p> <p><strong>Drizzle</strong> with the remaining sauce&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Enjoy!</strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
